#Get timeline 
user_timeline=twitter.get_user_timeline(screen_name='AppleMusic',count=1)#Taking tweets from AppleMusic ID on twitter
#get most recent id
print(user_timeline)
last_id = user_timeline[0]['id']-1
for i in range(16):
    batch = twitter.get_user_timeline(screen_name='AppleMusic',count=400, max_id=last_id)#Taking 400 tweets from AppleMusic twitter handle
    user_timeline.extend(batch)
    last_id = user_timeline[-1]['id'] - 1

Step 3 : Cleaning all the data

In [9]:
#Create a string form of our list of text
raw_string = ''.join(raw_tweets)
no_links = re.sub(r'http\S+', '', raw_string)
no_unicode = re.sub(r"\\[a-z][a-z]?[0-9]+", '', no_links)
no_special_characters = re.sub('[^A-Za-z ]+', '', no_unicode)
In [10]:
words = no_special_characters.split(" ")
words = [w for w in words if len(w) > 2]  # ignore a, an, be, ...
words = [w.lower() for w in words]
words = [w for w in words if w not in STOPWORDS]
